data.text:
Dear contestants,

In this Dress Rehearsal, you are given two interactive problems for practice purposes.  However, we would like you to know in advance that there will be no interactive problem in the 2019 World Finals tomorrow.

> Is there test support?

Yes. See the last paragraph of the Addendum to Judging Notes document.

> Does the judge adapt to the interaction or is the answer set beforehand

The answer does not have to be fixed beforehand.

> "your program makes the same move(direction) from the same cell twice"
> does it means that he can't make a consecutive moves in same cell twice ? I
> mean if I returned to the same cell after some moves, can I make a move I
> did on it before?

If you return to the same cell after some moves then make a move you already made, then that is a Wrong Answer.
